#####################################################################
# SFS Lab
#
# Student handout directory
#####################################################################

This directory contains the files needed to work through the SFS lab. It is
arranged as a handout-style working directory: start here, edit `sfs-disk.c`,
and use the provided tools to test your work.

Student source file:

    sfs-disk.c
        This is the file you modify while doing the lab.

Provided support files:

    sfs-api.h
        API specification for sfs-disk.c.

    sfs-disk.h
        On-disk data structures and constants.

    sfs-support.c
        Low-level disk image and mmap support.

    sfs-fsck.c
        Filesystem consistency checker.

    traces/
        Lua-style trace catalog. These files document the intended A/B/C test
        shape but are not executed by the current local grader.

Offline-only local tools:

    local/test-sfs.c
        Standalone local autograder.

    local/sfs-baseline-ref.c
        Coarse-lock reference implementation for performance calibration.

    Makefile
        Builds the local tools. Run `make`, then `make baseline`, then
        `./test-sfs`.

Read SFS_Lab_Writeup.md for the lab narrative and
local/OFFLINE_SELF_STUDY.md for the differences between this offline package
and the course infrastructure. Read local/SCORING.md before treating a local
score as meaningful.
